Application Process | UIC Admissions                  Explore UIC  Visit Virtually  Apply    S      Search Input     Submit        M       Application Process        Home  Undergraduate  You are here     Home  Undergraduate  You are here                          Due to the COVID-19 pandemic UIC continues to accept undergraduate first-year and transfer applications for the Fall 2020 semester.        Translations       Arabic     Chinese     Indonesian     Korean     Portuguese     Russian     Spanish     Thai     Turkish     Vietnamese             Before You Apply    Start planning now.  Early preparation is the key to successfully beginning your journey at UIC.  Do your research.  Learn all about UIC . Explore which programs are a good fit for your goals. Find out about financial aid options. The more you know, the easier it will be to navigate the application process.  Know your deadlines.  Keep track of all deadlines that apply to you. Keep in mind, some programs and departments, such as GPPA and Honors College have their own deadlines.  Check your requirements.  Familiarize yourself with admission requirements , including department, test, and course requirements, as soon as possible.  Begin essays and request recommendations.  Your application essay and recommendations are an opportunity to make your application stand out. Starting early ensures you and your recommenders have adequate time to meet deadlines.         Applying for Admission    Ready to apply? Complete these steps.  Before submitting your application, make sure you check requirements & deadlines for specific requirements based on how you are applying.  FIrst Year Applicants: complete the Common Application .  Transfer Applicants: complete the UIC Web Application .  Submit your application fees or application waiver.  Submit essays or letters of recommendation.  Have your transcripts sent.  Send in test scores.         After you apply    Your application is in. What's next?  Check application status.  You can check your status online. This is where you’ll find a checklist of items we’ve received and which items are still outstanding.  When you can expect to hear from us.  You'll receive a decision by email or mail within the time frames below.  First Year applicants: October–March Transfer applicants: Spring term: September–December Fall term: February–May  Questions about your application?   FAQs  Document Upload Guide  Undergraduate Appeal Process  Contact us at (312) 996-4350         After Acceptance    Congratulations, you're in! Now what?  Follow this newly admitted student checklist to help you stay on track and take advantage of all UIC has to offer.                       Already applied? Check your application status Check Status           Related Resources    Undergraduate Admissions Deadlines  Honors College  GPPA  UIC Academic Calendar                    UnderGraduate      Graduate & Professional                 Office of Admissions  Main Office  1200 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 996-4350 Contact UIC Admissions    Visitors Center  1220 West Harrison Street Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Phone: (312) 413-1726                 Mailing Address  Undergraduate  Office of Undergraduate Admissions (MC 018) University of Illinois at Chicago 1200 West Harrison Street, Suite 1100 Chicago, IL 60607-7161 Contact Undergraduate Admissions     Graduate & Professional  The graduate and professional application process is paperless. Please do not mail materials unless expressly requested. Contact Graduate and Professional Admissions                             Privacy Statement  Nondiscrimination Statement  Site Map  Accessibility  Site Home  UIC Home  Login  Webmaster  Copyright © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois Facebook  Twitter  YouTube  Accessibility         T     CookieSettings     